  <prompt>
    REWRITE the `.claude/skills/jps-playbook-audit/SKILL.md` body to audit existing playbooks AGAINST
    the new R7 node-first dispatch model. The audit's job is to find drift between the existing 94
    spaarkedev1 playbook nodes (or any owner-imported playbook) and the new canonical contract.

    The audit must:
    - VALIDATE every node has `sprk_executortype` Choice set to a valid enum value.
    - FLAG legacy `sprk_nodetype` Dataverse-column references (column is REMOVED in Wave 4).
    - FLAG Actions with stale dispatch signals (`sprk_actiontypeid` lookup row references, `sprk_executoractiontype` INT) — these are decorative-only or dropped post-R7.
    - FLAG prompt-driven executors with NULL Action FK.
    - FLAG pure executors with non-NULL Action FK.
    - VERIFY scope hints + ADR-037 compose strategy unchanged.

    Cite the §3.1 WHY (R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion) so future operators understand WHY
    these drift patterns exist and are dangerous.

    **Sub-Agent Write Boundary applies — main session executes this. No parallel dispatch.** Per CLAUDE.md §3.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior skill author for the Spaarke skill library. You understand both legacy dispatch (3-layer
    Action → lookup row drift) and the R7 single-hop model. Your job: rewrite the audit skill so it
    surfaces exactly the drift patterns Wave 5 backfill addresses (94 spaarkedev1 nodes) PLUS the
    drift patterns future owner-imported playbooks may carry.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Updated `.claude/skills/jps-playbook-audit/SKILL.md` that:
    1. Validates every node has `sprk_executortype` Choice set; flags NULL or invalid values.
    2. Flags legacy `sprk_nodetype` Dataverse-column references (REMOVED in Wave 4 schema cleanup).
    3. Flags Actions with stale dispatch signals: `sprk_actiontypeid` lookup row references or `sprk_executoractiontype` INT signals (decorative-only post-R7 per FR-05).
    4. Flags prompt-driven executors (AiAnalysis, AiCompletion, AiEmbedding) with NULL Action FK.
    5. Flags pure executors (Condition, Start, ReturnResponse, EntityNameValidator, etc.) with non-NULL Action FK.
    6. Verifies compose strategy + scope hints (ADR-037) unchanged.
    7. Cites the §3.1 WHY (R3.1 history of dispatch-model confusion) so future operators understand drift dangers.
    8. Produces an audit report shape that mirrors the Wave 5 review tool output (sanity alignment).
    9. `last-reviewed: 2026-06-28`; `Reviewed By: R7 task 072 (FR-32)`.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="rewrite-target">.claude/skills/jps-playbook-audit/SKILL.md</file>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
