  <context>
    <background>
      jps-playbook-audit currently audits playbooks under the legacy 3-layer model — checking that Action's
      `sprk_actiontypeid` lookup row's `sprk_executoractiontype` matches the executor that the runtime
      would dispatch. R7 collapses that to one hop. The audit becomes simpler structurally — but it MUST
      flag the legacy patterns so owner-imported playbooks (or stale CI/CD-deployed playbooks) surface
      their drift.

      Sequential order in Wave 7: task 071 (jps-playbook-design) shipped Executor-first mental model; this
      task ships the inverse — auditing existing playbooks against that model.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="071" status="prerequisite">jps-playbook-design rewrite must complete first for aligned terminology.</dependency>
      <dependency task="024" status="prerequisite">Wave 2 single-hop dispatch refactor merged.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Wave 5 task 050 (Review-PlaybookNodes-Dispatch.ps1) is the scripted version of this audit. Skill body should mirror its output shape.</item>
      <item>Wave 4 (FR-03, FR-04) drops the legacy fields; audit must flag any playbook still referencing them as a deploy-script bug.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: skill body rewrite (not ADR-bound code) · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-32, FR-03, FR-04, FR-05, FR-19 + design.md §2 invariants 1-3 + §3.1 WHY.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read existing skill body">
      Read full current `.claude/skills/jps-playbook-audit/SKILL.md` (~14 KB).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read aligned prior rewrites">
      Read tasks 070 + 071 outputs for terminology alignment + cross-references.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Inventory legacy audit logic">
      Grep skill body for: "ActionType lookup", "sprk_actiontypeid", "sprk_executoractiontype", "3-layer", "lookup row". Each is rewrite-target.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Rewrite Purpose + Applies When">
      Reframe: "Audits existing playbooks against the R7 node-first dispatch contract. Flags drift between deployed Dataverse rows and the canonical single-hop model."
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Rewrite audit checklist">
      New audit steps (the load-bearing rewrite):
      A. Every node row has `sprk_executortype` set to a valid Choice value (not NULL, not 0-default).
      B. Every node's `sprk_nodetype` Dataverse-column reference is FLAGGED (column removed Wave 4).
      C. Every Action row's `sprk_actiontypeid` lookup column carries decorative-only meaning post-R7; FLAG runtime use (browse-only is fine per FR-05).
      D. Every Action row's `sprk_executoractiontype` INT column is FLAGGED — dropped in Wave 4 (FR-04).
      E. Prompt-driven executors (executor type 1/2/9 etc — AiCompletion/AiAnalysis/AiEmbedding) have non-NULL `sprk_actionid` FK.
      F. Pure executors (Condition, Start, ReturnResponse, EntityNameValidator, etc.) have NULL `sprk_actionid` FK.
      G. Compose strategy + scope hints unchanged per ADR-037 — verify untouched by audit.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Insert R7 dispatch-model section">
      Short subsection: "## The R7 dispatch model — what changed and why" citing design.md §3.1 + §2 Invariants 1-3. Explicit WHY: 3-layer storage drift was the root cause; audit's job is to surface playbooks still carrying that drift.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Define audit report shape">
      Output schema (mirrors Wave 5 review tool CSV):
      | node-guid | playbook-name | node-name | current sprk_executortype | sprk_nodetype (legacy, expect NULL) | Action FK | Action ActionType lookup (decorative) | Drift flags | Recommended action |
      Document the shape inline so a manual audit produces results compatible with the scripted Wave 5 tool.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Update validation guidance">
      Validate strictly against `sprk_executortype` Choice values. ANY reliance on Action's lookup row for dispatch = audit FAIL.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Bump frontmatter">
      `last-reviewed: 2026-06-28`; `Reviewed By: spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7 task 072 (FR-32 — node-first audit)`.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Verify acceptance">
      Re-read rewritten skill body. Confirm: (a) audit checklist enumerates 7 drift patterns A-G, (b) §3.1 WHY cited inline, (c) report shape aligns with Wave 5 CSV tool, (d) frontmatter bumped.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 072 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 073.
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Commit-deferred">
      DO NOT commit. Wave 7 commits at task 075.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
